    "For detailed calculations, refer to Supplementary Note 1.",
    "A SiO 2 /Si substrate was coated with a 200-nm-thick TiN layer by sputtering.",
    "The TiN layer was then patterned onto the CA bottom electrode (BE) using conventional photolithography and inductively coupled plasma (ICP)-reactive ion etching.",
    "The ICP and substrate bias powers were maintained at 200 and 20 W, respectively, during the TiN etching process.",
    "Etching was performed using Ar and Cl 2 gases at flow rates of 5 and 30 standard cubic centimeters per minute, respectively."
